author: H M CHAITHANYA SWAMY AND NIRANJAN KAGGERE
description: A senior police officer's warning about security risks at RCB's IPL victory celebration was ignored, leading to a stampede that killed 11. The officer had cautioned against the event at Vidhana Soudha due to potential overcrowding and inadequate security. Political figures are now demanding accountability from top officials for allegedly rushing the event without proper safety measures, despite prior warnings.
title: Bengaluru stampede: Cops had warned against feting RCB at legislature

author: TNN
description: Recent World Bank data reveals a significant decline in India's extreme poverty rate, dropping from 27.1% in 2011-12 to 5.3% in 2022-23, lifting nearly 270 million people out of extreme poverty. This reduction is attributed to updated poverty line definitions and improved household survey data. Free food transfers and a narrowing rural-urban poverty gap also contributed to this progress.
title: Despite West Bengal raising threshold, India achieves big dip in extreme poverty

author: SRINATH VUDALI
description: Telangana Anti Narcotics Bureau busted an inter-state hawala racket linked to international drug cartels, seizing ₹50 lakh from a Goa flat, ready to be laundered to Nigeria. The investigation revealed that the key accused, Uttam Singh, laundered ₹2.1 crore of drug money in a week through informal channels, with funds ultimately destined for Nigeria.
title: Drug cartel's hawala cash trail ends in washing machine in Goa

author: TNN
description: Rahul Gandhi has criticized the Election Commission after it refuted his rigging allegations in the 2024 Maharashtra assembly election. Gandhi demands the EC to release consolidated, digital voter rolls and post-5 pm CCTV footage from Maharashtra polling booths. He claims the BJP is rigging elections by adding fake voters and inflating turnout, damaging institutions and public trust.
title: Maharashtra polls were match-fixed, Bihar next: Rahul Gandhi

author: TNN
description: Pakistan's aspirations to lead multiple key UN Security Council terrorism-related committees have been largely unmet, securing only the chairship of the 1988 Taliban Sanctions Committee. Other UNSC members rebuffed Pakistan's demands for leadership roles, leading to delays in committee allocations. India views this outcome as a reflection of Pakistan's limited standing and credibility within the UN.
title: Pakistan's demand to chair 4 UN terror-related panels snubbed, finally given only one

The government aims to prevent future occurrences through thorough investigation and cooperation.

description: Kabul is facing a severe water crisis, potentially becoming the first modern city to completely run out of water. title: 'Match-fixing will come to Bihar next': Rahul accuses BJP of 'rigging' Maha polls

author: TOI SPORTS DESK
description: Tom Brady ignited NBA fan debate by revealing his Mount Rushmore of GOATs, notably including Michael Jordan and Kobe Bryant while omitting LeBron James. The list also featured WNBA stars like Caitlin Clark and A'ja Wilson, alongside athletes from various sports, sparking controversy among fans who questioned the exclusion of James and the inclusion of newer players.
title: NBA fans react as Brady leaves James off GOAT list; Clark, Reese make cut

author: TOI WORLD DESK
description: Immigration sweeps by ICE agents in Los Angeles, including at Home Depot locations, sparked widespread protests and a tense standoff. Demonstrators rallied against the enforcement actions, leading to over 40 arrests and clashes with law enforcement. The protests intensified after the arrest of SEIU California President David Huerta, who was accused of obstructing federal agents.
title: Smoke bombs, protests, arrests: Tensions soar in Los Angeles after ICE raids

author: TOI SPORTS DESK
description: At Puja Pujara's book launch, Rohit Sharma shared a humorous anecdote from a 2012 West Indies tour, recalling how Cheteshwar Pujara was mobbed after venturing out late for vegetarian food. Sharma also lauded Pujara's resilience in overcoming ACL injuries to play over 100 Tests.
title: Watch: Rohit shares unknown story of Pujara from 2012 during event

author: TOI SPORTS DESK
description: Marco Jansen revealed Ricky Ponting's playful parting words as he gears up for the World Test Championship Final against Australia. Jansen, fresh from a successful IPL season, valued Ponting's positive coaching approach. He also looks forward to learning from Stuart Broad, who joined the Proteas as a consultant, to gain insights on facing the Australian team at Lord's.
title: WTC Final: Jansen reveals Ponting's cheeky send-off - 'Good luck, but ...'

author: DWAIPAYAN GHOSH
description: Bengal police filed a charge sheet regarding the Murshidabad violence. The violence resulted in the deaths of Harogobindo Das and his son Chandan. A rumour about a mosque attack triggered the incident. Police arrested thirteen individuals from Bengal, Odisha, and Jharkhand. The accused face charges including murder and armed robbery. The Das family seeks a CBI probe.
title: Jafrabad double murder: 55 days on, chargesheet names 13

author: TOI WORLD DESK
description: Russia launched a massive aerial assault on Ukraine, deploying over 400 drones and 40 missiles, resulting in casualties and widespread damage across six regions. The attack, which killed at least six and injured around 80, targeted residential areas and critical infrastructure, prompting condemnation from President Zelenskyy.
title: 400 drones, 40 missiles: Footage shows Russia's attacks on Ukraine; watch video

author: TOI BUSINESS DESK
description: Tesla's shares plummeted following a public feud between Elon Musk and Donald Trump, triggered by Musk's criticism of Trump's tax bill. This clash exacerbated existing challenges, making Tesla the worst-performing large-cap stock this year. Despite a slight rebound, the fallout raises concerns about Tesla's future amid political and regulatory uncertainty, impacting investor confidence.
title: Caught in Trump-Musk crossfire: Tesla stock sinks amid feud

author: TOI SPORTS DESK
description: Following his semi-final defeat by Jannik Sinner at Roland Garros, Novak Djokovic hinted at a possible farewell to the Parisian crowd. The 38-year-old, a three-time champion, expressed gratitude for the support he received, stating it might be his last match there.
title: French Open: 'Honoured' Djokovic hints at farewell; loses to Sinner

author: TOI NEWS DESK
title: G7 summit: Carney asked why PM Modi was invited; here's how he responded

author: TOI SPORTS DESK
description: Magnus Carlsen clinched his seventh Norway Chess title after D Gukesh's loss to Fabiano Caruana in the final round. Carlsen secured the championship with 16 points, closely followed by Caruana and Gukesh. In the women's section, Anna Muzychuk of Ukraine emerged victorious, despite losing the Armageddon tie-break, while Koneru Humpy finished as the runner-up.
title: Norway Chess: Gukesh falters in final round; Carlsen clinches 7th title

author: TOI SPORTS DESK
description: Magnus Carlsen clinched his seventh Norway Chess title, benefiting from D Gukesh's final-round loss to Fabiano Caruana. Carlsen drew his last game, securing the win with 16 points, while Caruana finished second. Carlsen acknowledged the potential of young Indian talents like Gukesh and Arjun Erigaisi, highlighting his own challenging tournament, including a notable loss to Gukesh.
title: 'Not a positive memory': Carlsen haunted by Gukesh loss; but says 'Indians need time'

author: TOI WORLD DESK
description: A public fallout has occurred between Donald Trump and Elon Musk, once allies. Musk proposed "The America Party" after a poll on X, fueled by his vision to dismantle the establishment. The rift escalated after Musk criticized Trump's legislative efforts, leading to Trump threatening to terminate Musk's government subsidies and contracts.
title: 'The America Party': Amid spat with Trump, is Musk eyeing third front?

author: RAJENDRA PRASAD SHARMA
description: In Alwar, a shocking incident occurred at ESIC Medical College where a 32-year-old woman, recovering from a tubectomy in the surgical ICU, was allegedly raped by a nursing staff member. Following the husband's complaint and the woman's disclosure, police have registered a case, and the accused, Subhash Ghithala, has been barred from the hospital.
title: Patient raped in ICU of Rajasthan hospital by nursing staffer

author: AMIT KUMAR
description: KL Rahul, known for his adaptability and resilience, faces a significant opportunity in the upcoming England series. With senior players like Virat Kohli and Rohit Sharma absent, Rahul emerges as the most experienced Indian batter on English soil. His childhood coach emphasises his mental fortitude and technical foundation built on red-ball cricket, expecting a matured performance.
title: IND vs ENG: No more musical chairs! For KL Rahul, England could finally be home

author: TOI WORLD DESK
description: US officials, including Treasury Secretary Scott Bessent, are set to meet in London for trade negotiations, announced President Trump. This follows a conversation with Chinese President Xi Jinping amidst ongoing trade tensions. Despite recent tariff reductions after Geneva talks, concerns remain.
title: Trade war: US-China trade talks next week; Trump says 'meet should go well'

author: TOI ENTERTAINMENT DESK
description: Akshay Kumar's 'Housefull 5' hit theaters on June 6, 2025, with two alternate endings. The film has garnered ₹23 crore on its opening day, surpassing 'Housefull 4' and 'Sky Force'. With an ensemble cast and a murder mystery plot set on a cruise ship, the movie has witnessed a 28.88% occupancy rate, peaking during night shows.
title: ‘Housefull 5’ box office collection: Akshay starrer collects Rs 23 cr on its first day

author: STEFFY THEVAR
description: In a miraculous recovery, a 20-year-old college student regained his voice after a severe accident in Chakan. He crashed his two-wheeler into a pickup truck, embedding 33 glass pieces in his throat. Doctors at a private hospital successfully removed the glass during a critical surgery, repairing damaged blood vessels and nerves near his voice box.
title: 'Everything went dark': Crash leaves Maha biker with 33 glass pieces in throat

author: ARSHAD AFZAAL KHAN
description: The Ram Temple in Ayodhya has been adorned with 45 kilograms of pure gold, valued at approximately Rs 50 crore, as confirmed by Nripendra Mishra. This gold has been used in the temple's doors and Lord Ram's throne. While the main structure is complete, other facilities are still under construction and are expected to be completed by December 2025.
title: 'Golden doors, throne': Ayodhya Ram temple uses 45kg of pure gold worth Rs 50cr

author: TOI LIFESTYLE DESK
description: Eid ul-Adha, a significant day for Muslims globally, commemorates Prophet Ibrahim's devotion and is celebrated with prayers, gratitude, and charitable giving. Families honor the occasion by sacrificing an animal and sharing it with loved ones and those in need.
title: 75+ messages, greetings, wishes and quotes for Eid-ul-Adha 2025

author: TNN
description: Indian investigators have identified Nasir, a former Pakistan Police sub-inspector turned YouTuber, as a key ISI handler in cross-border espionage. He and Naushaba Shehzad allegedly cultivated Indian influencers, offering visas and luxury accommodations in exchange for pro-Pakistan content. This operation aimed to create a favorable narrative and gather intelligence, with connections leading to expelled officials and arrested YouTubers.
title: Espionage network exposed: Ex-Pak cop-turned-YouTuber groomed influencers for ISI

author: CH SUSHIL RAO
description: In Telangana's Adilabad, Inspector Bandari Raju cleverly disguised himself as a farmer to bust a loan fraud racket. Donning a lungi and towel, he infiltrated the group of agents who were exploiting vulnerable farmers by siphoning off money from their loan amounts.
title: 'Lungi, not lathi': 34 arrested after T'gana cop busts farmer loan scam
